news_header: Nordea's operating profit for Q3 was EUR 1.6 billion, a 5% decrease year-on-year.
news_text: In the period from July to September, Nordea reported an operating profit of EUR 1.6 billion, reflecting a 5% decline compared to the same period last year. The bank's net interest income fell to €1.9 billion, while net remuneration income rose by 4% and business returns increased by 2%. CEO Frank Vang-Jensen noted that the Group's positive development continued in the third quarter, maintaining a good level of profitability.
